(283, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable word from the box. There are more words than needed. Make any grammatical change if necessary.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/12cd4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nUniversities should never be made into mechanical organizations for collecting and distributing knowledge. Through them the people should (a) &mdash; their intellectual hospitality, their wealth of mind to others, and earn their (b) &mdash; right in return to (c) &mdash; gifts from the rest of the world. But in the (d) &mdash; length and breadth of India there is not a (e) &mdash; university established in the modern time where a foreign or an Indian student can (f) &mdash; be acquainted with the best (g) &mdash; of the Indian mind. For that we have to cross the sea, and (h) &mdash; at the doors of France and Germany. Educational institutions in our country are Indian&rsquo;s alms-bowl of (i) &mdash;; they lower our intellectual self-respect; they encourage us to make a foolish (j) &mdash; of decorations composed of borrowed feathers.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
