(289, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the text below and fill in the blanks with suitable word from the box. There are more words in the box than necessary. Make any grammatical change if necessary.</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/18cd4.PNG\" />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<br />\r\nProper education (a) ___ a learner with opportunities (b) ___ all his talents. Its aim is to (c) ___ him physically and (d) ___ so that he can also be (e) ___ to himself and to the society. An educated man is (f) ___ but he also (g) ___ others in attaining self-reliance. He is supposed to be well-mannered, kind and (h) ___. So a man who has acquired knowledge and skill only for his material development cannot be (i) ___ a truly (j) ___ man.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(290, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable words from the box. There are more words than needed. Make any grammatical change if necessary.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/65co4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nWe waited for the asparagus to be (a) ___. Panic seized me. It was not a question now of how much (b) ___ I should have left for the rest of the month, but whether I (c) ___ enough to pay the bill. It would be (d) ___ to find myself ten francs short and obliged to (e) ___ from my guest. I could not bring (f) ___ to do that. I knew exactly how much I had and if the bill (g) ___ to more, I made up my mind that I would (h) ___ my hand in my pocket and with a dramatic cry start up and say it had been (i) ___. Of course, it would be awkward if she had not money enough either to pay the bill. Then the only thing would be to leave my watch and say I would come back and (j) ___ late.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(291, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable word from the box. There are more words than needed. Make any grammatical change if necessary.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/66co4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nConflict can be defined as (a) ___ of value and ideas among other things, and the most serious form of conflict is (b) ___ clashes that result in lot of (c) ___ and casualties. There can be conflict (d) ___ us, which is (e) ___ intrapersonal conflict. The conflict between or (f) ___ persons is called (g) ___ conflict. Constraints of economic resources is also a cause of conflict and it is known as (h) ___ conflict. Conflict is a very (i) ___ phenomenon, but sometimes it takes (j) ___ forms.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(292, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Fill in the gaps with suitable words from the following list. There are more words in the list than you need. (Make any grammatical changes if necessary).</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/69co4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nAll of us know what a dream is. Generally we dream during our sleep. Dream may appear to be short or long lasting. Sometimes we say, I dream for the whole night! But do we really dream for the whole night? Some dreams are sweet or (a) ___. Some are horrible. When we dream something extremely bad, we call it a (b) ___. This is interesting that dreams have no (c) ___. They are soft, (d) ___ and (e) ___. Do you know how the words (f) ___ and (g) ___ differ from dream? Do you know any (h) ___? What do they do? Does dream have any relation with (i) ___? Do we always dream during our sleep? The dream we have during the day time (j) ___ day-dream. Sometimes we long for something so passionately. We call that a dream as well.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(293, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable word from the box. There are more words than needed. Make any grammatical change if necessary.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=05<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/70co4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nHercules was (a) &mdash; to Jupiter and Alcmena. He was very powerful, (b) &mdash; and successful. King Eurystheus, his cousin made him do some (c) &mdash; jobs, which are known as &quot;twelve labours of Hercules&quot; in Greek mythology. One of them was a (d) &mdash; against a terrible lion. Hercules (e) &mdash; the lion with his own hands and (f) &mdash; it to the king. Again, he (g) &mdash; a monster named the Hydra with the (h) &mdash; of his servant Iolaus. He (i) &mdash; reputation of a hero throughout the (j) &mdash; .&quot;</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(294, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Fill in the gaps with appropriate word from the box in each gap.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=05<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/71co4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nKeeping promise given to anyone is a must though it takes much perseverance to keep promise honestly. Since keeping promise is a (a) ___ of remembrance, we should be (b) ___ whenever we make promises. While (c) ___ an unavoidable danger, people usually (d) ___ any promise only to be (e) ___ from the situation without perfect (f) ___. After being rescued most people (g) ___ forget the promises given. A (h) ___ about the pipe piper of Germany (i) ___ how the piper was deliberately (j) ___ by the mayor, who has made promises to give piper one thousand guilders for his works.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(295, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable word from the box. There are more words than needed. Make any grammatical change if necessary</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=05<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/73co4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nBeauty is easy to appreciate but difficult to define. As we look (a) ___, we discover beauty in (b) ___ objects and sights in nature, in the (c) ___ of children, in the (d) ___ of strangers. But asked to (e) ___, we run into (f) ___. Does beauty have an (g) ___ objective identity? Is it universal, or is it (h) ___ on our sense perceptions? Does it lie in the eye of the (i) ___? &ndash;we ask ourselves. A further difficulty arises when beauty (j) ___ itself not only by its presence, but by its absence as well, as when we are repulsed by ugliness and desire beauty.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(296, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable words from the box. There are more words than needed. Make any grammatical change if necessary.&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=05<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/74co4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nSelf-employment means to create (a) ___ opportunity for (b) ___ by one&#39;s own effort. Various government organizations are trying to (c) ___ a congenial atmosphere for self-employment. Different NGO&#39;s have (d) ___ rendered their help. Livestock (e) ___, agricultural (f) ___, poultry (g) ___ are some of the (h) ___. There are many (i) ___ for self-employment in Bangladesh. One can (j) ___ engage oneself on these jobs.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(297, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable words from the box. There are more wards than necessary. You may change the form of the words if necessary</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<a href=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/19dha4.PNG\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/19dha4.PNG\" /></a><br />\r\nKuakata is truly a virgin beach and a (a) ___ for migratory winter birds. Fishing boats (b) ___ in the Bay of Bengal with colorful sails, (c) ___ waves and the lines of coconut trees add to the vibrant colours of Kuakata. The (d) ___ culture of the Rakhaine community and hundred year old Buddhist temples indicate the age-old tradition and (e) ___ heritage of this area. Kuakata is also a (f) ___ land for the Hindus and Buddhists. Each year thousands of devotees come here to attend the (g) ___ namely Rash Purnima and Maghi Purnima. On these two days, (h) ___ take holy bath and enjoy going to the traditional fairs. Kuakata is one of the most remarkable sea-beaches where visitors can watch both the sunrise and the (i) ___. So, it can be rightly (j) ___ the daughter of the sea.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(298, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable word from the box. There are more words than needed. Make any grammatical change if necessary.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/20dha4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nThe British-Bangladeshi community is one of the largest (a) ___ communities in the UK, which is also well established throughout the communities. Bangladeshis primarily live in the city of London, mainly in the East London (b) ___ of which the borough of Tower Hamlets has the highest percentage of Bangladeshis with about 33% of the borough&#39;s total population. The national (c) ___ of ethnicity and identity found over 500, 000 people had Bangladeshi (d) ___ in Britain. There is also a significant community in and around Westminster. People from current Bangladesh or entire Bengal or a broader region (e)  Bangladesh were first present in the United Kingdom when Sylhetis arrived as (f) ___ on ships from the 18th century to 19th century, and throughout the years this has created connections with Sylhet. Large numbers (g) ___ during the 1970s mainly from Sylhet region, for the need to find work and (h) ___ a better living. The influence of Bangladeshi culture and diversity can (i) ___ across London in boroughs such as Tower Hamlets, Newham, Camden and Southwark, The Street a of Brick Lane has a large history of Bangladeshis and has officially (j) ___ as &quot;Banglatown&quot;, which has hundreds of &quot;Indian&quot; restaurants nearly all owned by Sylheti Bangladeshis.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(299, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Fill in the gaps with suitable words from the box. Make any grammatical changes if necessary. </strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/21dha4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nA student or learner can improve all his latent talents through the (a) ___ of proper education. Proper education aims at (b) ___ him not only physically but also mentally. Such education (c) ___ him an ideal man. He can (d) ___ both himself and (e)___ to the way of (f) ___ and prosperity. A (g) ___ educated man is sympathetic, (h) ___ and kind. Indeed, proper (i) ___ makes him mentally and (j) ___ developed.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
