(301, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable words from the box. There are more words than necessary. You may change the form of the words, if necessary.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/23dha4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nThe recent (a) ___ of the Rohingya Muslims from the state of Arakan has (b) ___&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;the attention of the world people. This tragedy of the Rohingya Diaspora has resulted from the wholesale (c) ___ displayed by the Myanmar armed forces along with the so called Buddhist priests (d) ___&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;brutality and racial hatred have not (e) ___ even the innocent children. Finding no other way, these Arakani Muslims have fled to Bangladesh. While (f) ___ across the river Naf by country boats or rafts, many women and children received (g) ___ graves. The (h) ___ experience of the survivors has moved the people of Bangladesh with (i) ___ and many Bangladeshi people have extended their (j) ___ hands for the welfare of these worst victims of racism.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(302, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable word from the box. There are more words than needed. Make any grammatical change if necessary.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/24dha4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nEtiquette, the complex network of rules that govern good behavior and our social and business interactions, is always (i) ___ and changing as society changes. It reflects our cultural norms, generally accepted (ii) ___ codes, and the rules of various groups we belong to. It helps us show respect and (iii) ___ to others and makes others glad that we are with them. Without proper manners and etiquette, the customs of polite society would soon (iv) ___ and we would act more like animals and less like people. In earlier times, the rules of etiquette were used for two purposes: to remind people of their own status within society and to (v) ___ certain (vi) ___ on individuals within that society. In the Middle Ages and the Renaissance, for instance, etiquette dictated everything from how a person of inferior rank had to bow to a person of higher rank to how long a man had to spend (vii) ___ a woman before the two could marry. Even the way a person mourned was strictly (viii) ___ by rules of etiquette until as recently as the Civil War era in the United States. Over the centuries, as society has become more democratic, etiquette has become an excellent (ix) ___ of good manners, common sense, and rules of conduct that reflect cultural norms and the rules of our society as a whole rather than just one (x) ___ group within it. It has less to do with the fashion of the moment or who is in power and more to do with putting others at ease and an ethical code of conduct.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(303, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable words from the box. There are more words than needed. You may change the form of the words if necessary.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/25dha4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nIn our society, there are some people whom we cannot trust easily and there are some people whom we cannot (a) ___. They are not easy. They seem to be (b) ___, but they are dishonest. It is too difficult for general people to (c) ___ them. This kind of man is very intelligent, tactful, cunning and a good actor. As they are (d) ___ they have to tell a lot of lies. Only a wise and over talented person can be (e) ___ to find who is honest or not. The man who has (f) ___ a lot in his life never trusts anybody easily. He will trust him after (g) ___. An easy and simple hearted man is (h) ___ easily by the dishonest men. We should be (i) ___ of such kind of dishonest men and should (j) ___ them.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(304, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable word from the box. There are more words than need. Make any grammatical change if necessary.</strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/26dha4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nScientists have recently reported that the polar ice caps are melting. This is due to a rise in (a)  temperatures known as the &lsquo;Greenhouse Effect.&rsquo; Carbon dioxide is (b)  responsible for temperature rise in the atmosphere. The carbon dioxide is (c)  off when coal and oil are burnt. This gas is (d)  in the air and ice caps in the North and South poles are melting. This may (e)  lead to a rise in the sea levels which could (f)  many areas of the globe. The &lsquo;Greenhouse Effect&rsquo; is just one of the many (g)  changes, which are taking place in the environment. Tropical rain forests, which took fifty million years (h)  are being (i)  at the rate of fourteen acres per minute. The total area of the world&rsquo;s deserts is increasing every year. Many species of animal and plants are (j)  with the threat of extinction.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(305, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable word from the box. There are more words than needed. Making any grammatical change if necessary</strong>.&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/27dha4.PNG\" style=\"height:65px; width:372px\" /><br />\r\nThe number of elderly people in the country is (a) ___ day by day. But elderly people, (b) ___ in villages, remain without any (c) ___ from family (d) ___ and official agencies. Many of them pass their days without getting food and proper (e) ____ in their (f) ___. From a press report it is known to us that some 7.2 million people are (g) ___ people. It is true that our elderly people who are without any (h)___ of earning, should be given monthly allowance or old age (i) ___. In the late nineties of the past century, the government took up a project for extending direct (j) ___ to the vulnerable section of the elderly people.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(306, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable word from the box. There are more words than needed. Make any grammatical change if necessary.&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/28dha4.PNG\" />&nbsp; &nbsp;<br />\r\nHigher education in Britain has experienced a dramatic (a) ___. One in three young people now (b) ___ higher education (c) ___ to one in six in 1989. The number of graduates also has increased (d) ___. There are some 90 (e) ___ in Britain which offer a (f) ___ of courses in a wide range of subjects including (g) ___ arts subject as well as science technology. Over 90% students receive government (h) ___ covering tuition fees and a (i) ___ grant. Parents also (j) ___ the amount depending on their income. The overseas students have to pay very high tuition fees.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(307, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable words from the box. There are more words than needed. Make any grammatical changes if necessary.&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/29dha4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nIn 1998, six-year old Ryan Hreljac was shocked to learn that children in Africa had to walk many kilometers everyday just to get (a) ___ water. Ryan decided he (b) ___ to build a well for a village in Africa. By (c) ___ household chores and public speaking on clean water (d) ___, Ryan raised enough money with (e) ___ his first well (f) ___ in 1999 at the Angolo Primary School in a northern Ugandan (g) ___. Ryan&#39;s determination &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;(h) ___ to Ryan&#39;s Well Foundation, which has completed 667 projects in 16 countries, bringing (i) ___ to clean water and (j) ___ to more than 714,000 people.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(308, 2, 20, 86, '<p><strong>Read the following text and fill in the blanks with suitable words from the box. There are more words then necessary. You may change the form of the words if necessary.</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;0.5<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=5<br />\r\n<img alt=\"\" src=\"http://my.questionskit.com/uploads/questions/30dha4.PNG\" /><br />\r\nEducation is the process by which our mind develops through formal (a) ___ at an institution. It is mental and (b) ___ training. It provides opportunities of growth and helps to meet challenges to (c) ___ success. Moreover, the purpose of education is to (d) ___ an individual. The aim of education is also to train individuals to make right (e) ___. It ennobles our mind and refines our (f) ___. It broadens our outlook and removes (g) ___. It helps us to be (h) ___ of rights and responsibilities. Education furnishes us with an (i) ___ in expressing truth. Therefore, it is compared to light which dispels the (j) ___ of ignorance.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
