(313, 2, 20, 87, '<p><strong>Fill in the blanks with appropriate word in each gap.</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=10<br />\r\nMoney is power and can do much good and evil. It gives (a) ___ and delight. It (b) ___ do everything. A person without (c) ___ is a person to be pitied. Nobody pays (d) ___ respect to him. His friends do not (e) ___ him. He has to depend on the (f) ___ of others. In order to (g) ___ money, he does a lot of jobs. It is a must (h) ___ our life. But it does not necessarily (i) ___ happiness. Happiness is absolutely a (j) ___ matter.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(314, 2, 20, 87, '<p><strong>Fill in the blanks with appropriate word in each gap. </strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=10<br />\r\nA most important truth, which we are apt to forget, is that a teacher can never truly teach unless he is still learning himself. A lamp can never (a) &mdash; another lamp unless it continues to (b) &mdash; its own flame. The teacher who has come to the end of his subject, who has no (c) &mdash; traffic with his knowledge, but merely (d) &mdash; his lessons to his (e) &mdash;, can only (f) &mdash; their minds; he (g) &mdash; quicken them. Truth not only must inform but (h) &mdash;. If the inspiration dies out, and the information only accumulates, then truth loses its (i) &mdash;. The greater part of our learning in the school has been waste because, for most of our teachers, their subjects are like dead specimens of once living things, with which they have a learned acquaintance, but no communication of (j) &mdash; and love.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(315, 2, 20, 87, '<p><strong>Fill in the blanks with appropriate word in each gap. </strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=10<br />\r\nThe ___ (a), The first Internet, was invented in 1969 and the public only ___ (b) access to the World Wide Web ___ (c) in 1993. Today, just 22 years later, the web has___ (d) the dissemination of information, created a ___ (e) multi-trillion dollar economic ___ (f), played a role in revolutions, and has ___ (g) much of the globe. It has also ___ (h) it possible for people all over the planet to reach ___ (i) and touch ___ (j).</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(316, 2, 20, 87, '<p><strong>Fill in the blanks with appropriate word in each gap.</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=10<br />\r\n&#39;Tsunami&#39; is a Japanese word which means marine earthquake. It caused a great (a) ___ on life and property along the coastlines of India, Sri Lanka, Thailand and Indonesia. About 5 million people became (b) ___. We are fortunate enough that by the (c)___ of God, Bangladesh narrowly (d) ___ such a natural (e) ___. But if is not unknown to us that Bangladesh lies in (f) ___ earthquake zone. It still has (g) ___ for Bangladesh to save the (h) ___ region from any such colossal (i) ___ of Tsunami. Since nobody can predict the (j) ___ time of earthquake, we have to be careful and conscious from now on.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(317, 2, 20, 87, '<p><strong>Fill in the blanks with suitable words. Use only one word in each gap.</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=10<br />\r\nGlobal technology has (a) ___ an integral part of our quest (b) ___ leprosy. The rapid diagnostic (c) ___ for leprosy infection, for example, was (d) ___ in conjunction with a Brazilian company. This company combined IDRI&#39;s leprosy diagnostic antigens with a smart phone-based platform that standardizes the (e) ___ to accurately interpret results and get a (f) ___ value. The test requires just a single (g) ___ of blood, mixed (h) ___ a developing reagent. The appearance of two lines (i) ___ that the person is (j) ___ for leprosy.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(318, 2, 20, 87, '<p><strong>Fill in the blanks with appropriate word in each gap.</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=10<br />\r\nCultural assault (a) ___ the bad influence of foreign culture (b) ___ native culture. In the global world it is (c) ___ difficult to check this cultural aggression. (d) ___ the development (e) ___ the device of information and communication, it has become very (f) ___ for a nation&#39;s culture to be influenced by another country. The cultural areas are vast. The culture of dress pattern, ways of entertainment, music, songs even some important thoughts and ideas (g) ___ influenced (h) ___ cultural aggression of other countries. Our Bangladeshi culture is mostly (i) ___ because of cultural (j) ___.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(319, 2, 20, 87, '<p><strong>Fill in the blanks with suitable word in each gap. </strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=10<br />\r\nThough labour is sacred, child labour is a (a) ___. But in our country many children are engaged in different types of (b) ___ labour. Child labour should be (c) ___ by making (d) ___. Education should be made (e) ___ for the children. Poor parents should be paid (f) ___ to supplement the income and be asked to send their children to schools. Children (g) ___ from poor families should be given free books and other necessary things. People in general should be more human and (h) ___ in their (i) ___ towards the working (j) ___.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(320, 2, 20, 87, '<p><strong>Fill in each gap with an appropriate word.&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;1<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=10<br />\r\nStudent life is a life of (a) ___ for future struggle. To make him (b) ___ for the struggle, education is necessary. So, the first and foremost duty of a student (c) ___ to persecute his studies well. He who (d) ___ his lessons regularly (e) ___ well in the examination. On the (f) ___ , the student who wastes his time cuts a (g) ___ figure. It should be (h) ___ in mind that none can get back the (i) ___ time. If the students neglect their studies, they will suffer in the (j) ___ run.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(321, 2, 20, 87, '<p><strong>Fill in the blanks with appropriate word in each gap. </strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=10<br />\r\nWhen a girl (a) ___ married, she usually (b) ___ out of school and begins full-time work in her in-laws household. In the in-laws house, she is (c) ___. She becomes (d) ___ to all forms of abuse, including dowry-related (e) ___. In Bangladesh, it is still (f) ___ for a bride&#39;s family to (g) ___ dowry, despite the practice being (h) ___. Dowry demands can also (i) ___ after the wedding. For an adolescent bride, even if her in-laws are supportive, there are greater health risks in terms of (j) ___ and child birth.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
(322, 2, 20, 87, '<p><strong>Fill in the blanks with appropriate word in each gap.</strong> &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1<span class=\"math-tex\">\\(\\times\\)</span>10=10<br />\r\nThe proper (a) ___ of study involves regular and proper understanding. In order to (b) ___ the best benefit from study, we should read (c) ___ and intelligently. We should not study (d) ___ for the purpose of (e) ___ examinations. We should take genuine (f) ___ in our studies so that we can enjoy what we (g) ___. This will give us knowledge and wisdom and (h) ___ the horizon of our (i)___. We should, therefore, study not for immediate gains but for (j) ___ the wealth of our mind.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
