(383, 2, 20, 88, '<p><strong>Rearrange the following sentences to make a coherent order.&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;10<br />\r\ni)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;He was not writing on a paper, but on the back of an envelope.<br />\r\nii)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;It is one of the finest and the shortest speeches in the English language.<br />\r\niii)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;President Abraham Lincoln was going to Gettysburg, Pennsylvania by a trian.<br />\r\niv)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;The last words of the speech are: &quot;Government of the people, by the people, for the people shall not perish from the earth&quot;.<br />\r\nv)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;In the train, he was busy writing something.<br />\r\nvi)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;On the envelope, it was what he was going to say at the meeting.<br />\r\nvii)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;It was the 10th November 1863.&nbsp;<br />\r\nviii)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;In fact, the speech on the envelope is now famous as &quot;Gettysburg Address&quot;.&nbsp;<br />\r\nix)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;These words tell us what the best possible way of ruling a country is.&nbsp;<br />\r\nx)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;He was going there to speak at a meeting.</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
