(396, 2, 20, 88, '<p><strong>Rearrange the following sentences to make a coherent order.&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;10<br />\r\na)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Everyone praised him and the senate trusted and honoured him.<br />\r\nb)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Othello was a brave soldier who had risen to become a general.&nbsp;<br />\r\nc)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;He had shown his bravery in many bloody battles against the Turks.&nbsp;<br />\r\nd)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;He told them of deserts, caves and mountains high enough to touch the sky.<br />\r\ne)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Desdemona was fascinated by the stories and specially by the story of his life.&nbsp;<br />\r\nf)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Othello told them strange stories of battles he had fought in and places he had seen.<br />\r\ng)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Hearing it, she had to weep and she never became tired of listening to it.&nbsp;<br />\r\nh)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Brabantio, a rich senator of Venice, had only one child, a daughter named Desdemona.&nbsp;<br />\r\ni)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;He also told them of men who ate human flesh and of strange race of people whose heads were under their shoulders.&nbsp;<br />\r\nj)&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Brabantio often invited Othello to his house where he and his daughter listened in wonder to Othello as he spoke about his adventures.&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '', NULL, '', 1),
